CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper March 8, 1947, pg. 11, reads: "Wedding Party - Mr. and Mrs. Wilbert Hawkins posed with their wedding party for the photographer. Bridesmaids were Miss Dorothy Greenlee and Miss Marion Powell. Matron of honor was Mrs. Gloria Lane, the bride's sister. Best man was William Redman. The bride is the former Miss Virginia Sumlin. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Groom Wilbert Hawkins, and bride Virginia Sumlin Hawkins holding bouquet, posed in front of dark curtain
